round:yellow;\"|2 <span style=\"font-size:87%;\">M</span>\n|style=\"background:lime;\"|'''1''' <span style=\"font-size:87%;\">M</span>\n|style=\"background:lime;\"|'''1'''\n|R32 <span style=\"font-size:87%;\">M</span>\n|style=\"background:lime;\"|'''1''' <span style=\"font-size:87%;\">M</span>\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[The Amateur Championship]]\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|NT\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|NT\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|NT\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|NT\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|R32\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:yellow;\"|QF\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|\n|style=\"background:lime;\"|'''1'''\n|}\n\nJones retired after his Grand Slam in 1930, playing only his own tournament, The Masters. As an amateur golfer, he was not eligible to compete in the [[PGA Championship]].\n\n{| cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"font-size: 95%; border: #aaa solid 1px; border-collapse: collapse;text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n!Tournament!!1934!!1935!!1936!!1937!!1938!!1939!!1940!!1941!!1942!!1943!!1944!!1945!!1946!!1947!!1948\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Masters Tournament]]\n|T13||T25||33||T29||T16||T33||WD||40||T28||style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|NT||style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|NT||style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"|NT||T32||T55||50\n|}\n{{legend|lime|Win}}\n{{legend|yellow|Top 10}}\n{{legend|#eeeeee|Did not play}}\n<span style=\"font-size:87%;\">M</span> = Medalist<br/>\n<span style=\"font-size:87%;\">LA</span> = Low amateur<br/>\nNT = No tournament<br/>\nWD = Withdrew<br/>\nR32, R16, QF, SF = Round in which Jones lost in amateur match play<br/>\n\"T\" indicates a tie for a place\n\nSources for U.S. Open and U.S. Amateur,<ref>[http://63.240.106.229/ USGA Championship Database] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090622212453/http://63.240.106.229/ |date=June 22, 2009 }}</ref> British Open,<ref name=\"open\">{{cite web|url=http://www.theopen.com/en/History/OpenChampions.aspx#player=Bobby+JONES+ |accessdate=August 29, 2013 |title=Bobby Jones |publisher=theopen.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016164928/http://www.theopen.com/en/History/OpenChampions.aspx |archivedate=October 16, 2013 }}</ref> 1921 British Amateur,<ref name=\"lion\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.la84foundation.org/SportsLibrary/AmericanGolfer/1921/ag2411e.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100806175718/http://www.la84foundation.org/SportsLibrary/AmericanGolfer/1921/ag2411e.pdf |url-status=dead |archive-date=August 6, 2010 |title=You Can Still Hear the Lion's Roar |date=June 4, 1921 |page=24 |first=John G. |last=Anderson |journal=The American Golfer }}</ref> 1926 British Amateur,<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.la84foundation.org/SportsLibrary/AmericanGolfer/1926/ag2910g.pdf |title=Sweetser Smashes the Barrier |journal=The American Golfer |date=July 1926 |page=58 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616043328/http://www.la84foundation.org/SportsLibrary/AmericanGolfer/1926/ag2910g.pdf |archivedate=June 16, 2012}}</ref> 1930 British Amateur,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=GGgVawPscysC&dat=19300602&printsec=frontpage |title=Jones Wins: New British Amateur Golf Champion |newspaper=The Glasgow Herald |date=June 2, 1930 |page=11}}</ref> and The Masters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.masters.com/en_US/tournament/past_winners.html |title=Past Winners & Results |publisher=masters.com |accessdate=November 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Summary===\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n!Tournament !! Wins !! 2nd !! 3rd !! Top-5 !! Top-10 !! Top-25 !! Events !! Cuts made\n|-\n|align=left|[[Masters Tournament]]         ||  0 || 0 || 0 ||  0 ||  0 ||  3 || 12 ||  \u2013\n|-\n|align=left|[[U.S. Open (golf)|U.S. Open]] ||  4 || 4 || 0 ||  9 || 10 || 11 || 11 ||  11\n|-\n|align=left|[[The Open Championship]]      ||  3 || 0 || 0 ||  3 ||  3 ||  3 ||  4 ||  3\n|-\n|align=left|[[U.S. Amateur]]               ||  5 || 2 || 2 || 11 || 12 || 13 || 13 || 13\n|-\n|align=left|[[The Amateur Championship]]   ||  1 || 0 || 0 ||  2 ||  2 ||  3 ||  3 ||  \u2013\n|-\n!Totals                                    !! 13 !! 6 !! 2 !! 25 !! 27 !! 33 !! 43 !! 27\n|}\n*Most consecutive cuts made \u2013 21 (1916 U.S. Amateur \u2013 1930 U.S. Amateur)\n*Longest streak of top-10s \u2013 14 (1921 U.S. Open \u2013 1926 U.S. Amateur)\n\n===Other records===\nJones's four titles in the U.S. Open remain tied for the most ever in that championship, along with [[Willie Anderson (golfer)|Willie Anderson]], [[Ben Hogan]], and [[Jack Nicklaus]]. His four-second-place finishes in the U.S. Open place him second all-time with [[Sam Snead]] and Nicklaus. [[Phil Mickelson]] holds the dubious record with six (1999, 2002, 2004, 2006, 2009, 2013) second-place finishes. His five titles in the U.S. Amateur are a record. Jones was ranked as the fourth greatest golfer of all time by ''[[Golf Digest]]'' magazine in 2000. Nicklaus was first, Hogan second, and Snead third.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0HFI/is_7_51/ai_63015233 |title=50 Greatest Golfers of All Time: And What They Taught Us |accessdate=December 5, 2007 |last=Yocom |first=Guy |date=July 2000 |journal=[[Golf Digest]] }}</ref> Jones was ranked as the third greatest golfer of all time in a major survey published by ''Golf Magazine'', September 2009. Nicklaus was ranked first, with [[Tiger Woods]] second, Hogan fourth, and Snead fifth.<ref>''[[Golf Magazine]]'', September 2009.</ref>\n\n==Films==\n[[File:1933 Goudey Sport Kings 38 Bobby Jones.jpg|thumb|right|1933 [[Goudey]] Sport Kings card]]\nJones appeared in a series of short instructional films produced by [[Warner Brothers]] in 1931 titled ''How I Play Golf, by Bobby Jones'' (12 films) and in 1933 titled ''How to Break 90'' (six films). The shorts were designed to be shown in theaters alongside feature films, whereby \"would-be golfers of the country can have the Jones' instruction for the price of a theater ticket.\"<ref name=DH>[https://www.newspapers.com/clip/4129799/bobby_jones_in_picture_land/ \"Bobby Jones in Picture Land,\"] ''Albany [OR] Democrat-Herald,'' March 2, 1931, pg. 6.</ref> Jones indicated at the time of the making of the 1931 series that the films would be \"designed as instructive\" but not \"so complicated that a non-golfer can't understand them.\"<ref name=DH />\n\nActors and actresses, mostly under contract with Warner Brothers, but also from other studios, volunteered to appear in these 18 episodes. Some of the more well known actors to appear in the instructional plots included [[James Cagney]], [[Joe E. Brown (comedian)|Joe E. Brown]], [[Edward G. Robinson]], [[W.C. Fields]], [[Douglas Fairbanks, Jr.]], [[Richard Barthelmess]], [[Richard Arlen]], [[Guy Kibbee]], [[Warner Oland]] and [[Loretta Young]]. Various scenarios involving the actors were used to provide an opportunity for Jones to convey a lesson about a particular part of the game. The shorts were directed by the prolific [[George Marshall (director)|George Marshall]].\n\n'''Title list of the shorts:'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0427602/ |title= Bobby Jones (III) (1902\u20131971) |publisher=IMDb}}</ref> <br/>\n''How I Play Golf''\n*''The Putter'' (April 26, 1931, ''Film Daily'' review)\n*''Chip Shots'' (April 26)\n*''The Niblick'' (May 31)\n*''The Mashie Niblick'' (June 5)\n*''Medium Irons'' (July 5)\n*''The Big Irons'' (July 12)\n*''The Spoon'' (July 19)\n*''The Brassie'' (August 1)\n*''The Driver'' (August 30)\n*''Trouble Shots'' (September 13)\n*''Practice Shots'' (September 27)\n*''A Round of Golf'' (September 4)\n\n''How To Break 90''\n*''The Grip'' (April 17, 1933)\n*''Position and Backswing'' (May 15)\n*''Hip Action'' (May 20)\n*''Down Swing (The Downswing)'' (May 29)\n*''Impact'' (July 15)\n*''Fine Points'' (August 5)\n\nJones was the subject of the quasi-biographical 2004 feature film ''[[Bobby Jones: A Stroke of Genius]]'' in which he was portrayed by [[Jim Caviezel]]. The Jones legend was also used to create a supporting character in ''[[The Legend of Bagger Vance]]'' in 2000, portrayed by [[Joel Gretsch]], and the event where he called his own penalty is used for the fictional protagonist, Rannulph Junuh.\n\n==Books==\nJones authored several books on golf including ''Down the Fairway'' with Oscar Bane \"O.B.\" Keeler (1927), ''The Rights and Wrongs of Golf'' (1933), ''Golf Is My Game'' (1959), ''Bobby Jones on Golf'' (1966), and ''Bobby Jones on the Basic Golf Swing'' (1968) with illustrator Anthony Ravielli. The 300-copy limited edition of ''Down the Fairway'' is considered one of the rarest and most sought after golf books by collectors. To keep this book readily available to golfers, [[Herbert Warren Wind]] included a reproduction of ''Down the Fairway'' in his Classics of Golf Library.<ref>[http://www.classicsofgolf.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&products_id=86 Classics of Golf Library].</ref>\n\nJones has been the subject of several books, most notably ''The Bobby Jones Story'' and ''A Boy's Life of Bobby Jones'', both by O.B. Keeler. Other notable texts are ''The Life and Times of Bobby Jones: Portrait of a Gentleman'' by Sidney L. Matthew, ''The Greatest Player Who Never Lived'' by J. Michael Veron, and ''Triumphant Journey: The Saga of Bobby Jones and the Grand Slam of Golf'' by Richard Miller. Published in 2006, ''The Grand Slam'' by [[Mark Frost]] has received much note as being evocative of Jones's life and times.\n\nA special room is dedicated to Jones's life and accomplishments at the [[United States Golf Association Museum and Arnold Palmer Center for Golf History]] in [[Far Hills, New Jersey]].\n\n==Honors==\nIn 1981, the U.S. Postal Service issued an 18-cent stamp commemorating Jones.<ref>{{cite web | title = American Sports Personalities | publisher = United States Postal Service | url = http://www.uspsstamps.com/stamps/series/american-sports-personalities | accessdate = October 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Jones Global Sports==\nFounded in 2013, Jones Global Sports designs, develops, and sells apparel, accessories and golf equipment. The company has an exclusive, worldwide license agreement with the family of Bobby Jones (known as Jonesheirs, Inc.) for the use of the Bobby Jones name.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bobbyjones.com/ |title=Bobby Jones website |accessdate=October 17, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==U.S. national team appearances==\n'''Amateur'''\n*[[Walker Cup]]: [[1922 Walker Cup|1922]] (winners), 1924 (winners), 1926 (winners), [[1928 Walker Cup|1928]] (winners, playing captain), [[1930 Walker Cup|1930]] (winners, playing captain)\n\n==See also==\n{{commons category|Bobby Jones (golfer)}}\n{{Portal|Biography}}\n*[[Bobby Jones Open]]\n*[[Grand Slam (golf)#Career Grand Slam|Career Grand Slam champions]]\n*[[List of golfers with most PGA Tour wins]]\n*[[List of men's major championships winning golfers]]\n*[[List of people on the cover of Time Magazine: 1920s]]\n*[[List of ticker-tape parades in New York City]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130917150357/http://www.bobbyjones.com/golf-legend/ bobbyjones.com]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20121031155043/http://www.bobbyjonesgolfdvd.com/ bobbyjonesgolfdvd.com]\n*[http://www.worldgolfhalloffame.org/bobby-jones/ World Golf Hall of Fame] \u2013 Bobby Jones\n*{{Find a Grave|553|Bobby Jones}}\n*[http://www.gshf.org/ Georgia Sports Hall of Fame]\n*{{IMDb name|0427602|Bobby Jones}}\n*[http://ssa.nls.uk/film.cfm?fid=0311 Bobby Jones Receives Freedom Of St. Andrews (1958)] (archive film from the [[National Library of Scotland]]: [[Scottish Screen Archive]])\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Bobby Jones in the [[Men's major golf championships|major championships]]\n|list1={{U.S. Open champions}}\n{{The Open champions}}\n\n{{Men\u2019s Career Grand Slam Champion golfers}}\n}}\n{{U.S. Amateur champions}}\n{{Sullivan Award winners}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jones, Bobby}}\n[[Category:American male golfers]]<!-- Golf cats first -->\n[[Category:Amateur golfers]]\n[[Category:Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets men's golfers]]\n[[Category:Winners of men's major golf championships]]\n[[Category:Men's Career Grand Slam champion golfers]]\n[[Category:World Golf Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:Golf course architects]]\n[[Category:Golf writers and broadcasters]]\n[[Category:American instructional writers]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. short films]]\n[[Category:Golfers from Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n[[Category:Georgia (U.S. state) lawyers]]<!-- Career cats -->\n[[Category:20th-century American lawyers]]\n[[Category:United States Army Air Forces personnel of World War II]]<!-- Military cats -->\n[[Category:United States Army Air Forces officers]]\n[[Category:Marist School (Georgia) alumni]]<!-- Education cats, in chron. order-->\n[[Category:Georgia Tech alumni]]\n[[Category:Harvard College alumni]]\n[[Category:Emory University School of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:James E. Sullivan Award recipients]]<!-- Misc. cats -->\n[[Category:Recipients of the Silver Buffalo Award]]\n[[Category:American Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Atlanta]]\n[[Category:Neurological disease deaths in the United States]]\n[[Category:Burials at Oakland Cemetery (Atlanta)]]\n[[Category:1902 births]]<!-- Birth/death cats -->\n[[Category:1971 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "A.C.Butner", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bobby_Jones_(golfer)"}
{"title_page": "Geosmin", "text_new": "{{chembox\n| Watchedfields = changed\n| verifiedrevid = 447312555\n| Name = Geosmin\n| ImageFile = Geosmin Structural Formulae.svg\n| ImageSize = 150px\n| ImageName = Geosmin\n| IUPACName = (4''S'',4a''S'',8a''R'')-4,8a-dimethyloctahydronaphthalen-4a(2''H'')-ol\n| OtherNames = (4''S'',4a''S'',8a''R'')-4,8a-Dimethyl-1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8-octahydronaphthalen-4a-ol; 4,8a-Dimethyl-decahydronaphthalen-4a-ol; Octahydro-4,8a-dimethyl-4a(2''H'')-naphthalenol\n|Section1={{Chembox Identifiers\n| ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}}\n| ChemSpiderID = 27642\n| StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChI = 1S/C12H22O/c1-10-6-5-8-11(2)7-3-4-9-12(10,11)13/h10,13H,3-9H2,1-2H3/t10-,11+,12-/m0/s1\n| StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChIKey = JLPUXFOGCDVKGO-TUAOUCFPSA-N\n| CASNo_Ref = {{cascite|correct|??}}\n| CASNo = 19700-21-1\n| PubChem = 29746\n| ChEBI_Ref = {{ebicite|correct|EBI}}\n| ChEBI = 46702\n| SMILES = O[C@]12[C@H](CCC[C@]2(CCCC1)C)C\n| InChI = 1/C12H22O/c1-10-6-5-8-11(2)7-3-4-9-12(10,11)13/h10,13H,3-9H2,1-2H3\n/t10-,11+,12-/m0/s1\n  }}\n|Section2={{Chembox Properties\n| C=12|H=22|O=1\n| BoilingPtC = 270 to 271\n  }}\n|Section7={{Chembox Hazards\n| FlashPtC = 104\n  }}\n}}\n\n'''Geosmin''' is an [[organic compound]] with a distinct earthy flavor and aroma. This compound is responsible for the majority of taste and odor outbreaks in drinking water worldwide <ref>[https://aem.asm.org/content/73/14/4395/ Biochemical and Ecological Control of Geosmin\nand 2-Methylisoborneol in Source Waters], \"Applied and Environmental Microbiology\", Volume 73, July 2007.</ref>. Geosmin is also responsible for the earthy taste of [[beetroot]]s and a contributor to the strong scent ([[petrichor]]) that occurs in the air when rain falls after a dry spell of weather or when soil is disturbed.<ref>[http://www.expasy.org/spotlight/back_issues/035/ The earth's perfume], ''Protein Spotlight'', Issue 35, June 2003.</ref> \n\nIn chemical terms, it is a [[Bicyclic molecule|bicyclic]] [[alcohol]] with [[chemical formula|formula]] {{Chemical formula|C|12|H|22|O}}, a derivative of [[decalin]]. Its name is derived from the [[Ancient Greek]] {{lang|grc|[[wikt:\u03b3\u1fc6|\u03b3\u03b5\u03c9-]]}} {{transl|grc|ge\u014d-}} \"earth\" and {{lang|grc|[[wikt:\u1f40\u03c3\u03bc\u03ae|\u1f40\u03c3\u03bc\u03ae]]}} {{transl|grc|osm\u1e17}} \"smell\".  The word was coined in 1965 by the American biochemist Nancy N. Gerber (1929\u20131985) and the French-American biologist Hubert A. Lechevalier (1926\u20132015).<ref name=\"Gerber\" /><ref>[https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/geosmin Merriam-Webster dictionary:  geosmin ]</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n\nGeosmin is produced by various blue-green algae ([[cyanobacteria]]) and filamentous bacteria in the class [[Actinomyces]], and also some other prokaryotes and eukaryotes. The main genera in the cyanobacteria that have been shown to produce geosmin include ''[[Anabaena]]'', ''Phormidium'', and ''[[Planktothrix]]'', while the main genus in the Actinomyces that produces geosmin is ''[[Streptomyces]]''.  <ref>[https://aem.asm.org/content/73/14/4395/ Biochemical and Ecological Control of Geosmin\nand 2-Methylisoborneol in Source Waters], \"Applied and Environmental Microbiology\", Volume 73, July 2007.</ref>. <ref>{{cite journal | authors = Izaguirre G, Taylor WD. | year = 2004 | title = A guide to geosmin- and MIB-producing cyanobacteria in the United States | journal = Water Sci. Technol. | volume = 49 | issue = 9 | pages = 19\u201324 | pmid = 15237602| doi = 10.2166/wst.2004.0524 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | authors = Zaitlin B, Watson SB. | year = 2006 | title = Actinomycetes in relation to taste and odour in drinking water: Myths, tenets and truths | journal = Water Res. | volume = 40 | issue = 9 | pages = 1741\u201353 | pmid = 16600325 | doi = 10.1016/j.watres.2006.02.024}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | authors = Suurn\u00e4kki S, Gomez-Saez GV, Rantala-Ylinen A, Jokela J, Fewer DP, Sivonen K. | year = 2015 | title = Identification of geosmin and 2-methylisoborneol in cyanobacteria and molecular detection methods for the producers of these compounds | journal = Water Res. | volume = 68 | issue = 1 | pages = 56\u201366 | pmid = 25462716 | doi = 10.1016/j.watres.2014.09.037}}</ref> Communities whose [[water]] supplies depend on surface water can periodically experience episodes of unpleasant-tasting water when a sharp drop in the population of these bacteria releases geosmin into the local water supply. Under [[acid]]ic conditions, geosmin decomposes into odorless substances.<ref name = \"Gerber\">{{cite journal | pmid = 5866039 | volume=13 | issue=6 |date=November 1965 | pages=935\u20138 | last1 = Gerber | first1 = NN | last2 = Lechevalier | first2 = HA | title = Geosmin, an earthly-smelling substance isolated from actinomycetes. | pmc = 1058374 | journal = Applied Microbiology}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, the [[biosynthesis]] of geosmin by a bifunctional ''[[Streptomyces coelicolor]]'' [[enzyme]] was unveiled.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1021/ja062669x | volume = 128 | issue = 25 | pages = 8128\u20138129 | last1 = Jiang | first1 = J. | first2 = X. | last2 = He | first3 = D.E. | last3 = Cane | title = Geosmin biosynthesis. ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' germacradienol/germacrene D Synthase converts farnesyl diphosphate to geosmin | journal = [[J. Am. Chem. Soc.]] | year = 2006 | pmid = 16787064}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/nchembio.2007.29 | volume = 3| last1 = Jiang | first1 = J. | first2 = X. | last2 = He | first3 = D.E. | last3 = Cane | pmc = 3013058 | title = Biosynthesis of the earthy odorant geosmin by a bifunctional ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' enzyme | journal = [[Nat. Chem. Biol.]] | year = 2007 | pages = 711\u20135 | pmid = 17873868 | issue = 11}}</ref> A single enzyme, [[geosmin synthase]], converts [[farnesyl diphosphate]] to geosmin in a two-step reaction.\n\n''Streptomyces coelicolor'' is the model representative of a group of soil-dwelling bacteria with a complex lifecycle involving [[Mycelium|mycelial growth]] and [[spore formation]]. Besides the production of volatile geosmin, it also produces many other complex molecules of pharmacological interest; its [[genome]] sequence is available at the [[Sanger Institute]].<ref name=\"Sanger\">{{cite web |title=The genome of ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' A3(2) producing geosmin |publisher=Sanger Institute |url=http://www.sanger.ac.uk/Projects/S_coelicolor/ |accessdate=2009-01-31}}</ref>\n\n== Effects ==\n\nThe [[human nose]] is extremely sensitive to geosmin and is able to detect it at concentrations as low as 5 parts per trillion.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Polak | first1 = E.H. | last2 = Provasi | first2 = J. | title = Odor sensitivity to geosmin enantiomers | journal = Chemical Senses | volume = 17 | pages = 23\u201326 | year = 1992 | doi = 10.1093/chemse/17.1.23 }}</ref>\n\nGeosmin is responsible for the muddy smell in many commercially important freshwater fish such as [[carp]] and [[catfish]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Vallod|first=D.|last2=Cravedi|first2=J. P.|last3=Hillenweck|first3=A.|last4=Robin|first4=J.|date=2007-04-03|title=Analysis of the off-flavor risk in carp production in ponds in Dombes and Forez (France)|journal=Aquaculture International|language=en|volume=15|issue=3\u20134|pages=287\u2013298|doi=10.1007/s10499-007-9080-7|issn=0967-6120}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lovell|first=Richard T.|last2=Lelana|first2=Iwan Y.|last3=Boyd|first3=Claude E.|last4=Armstrong|first4=Martin S.|date=1986-05-01|title=Geosmin and Musty-Muddy Flavors in Pond-Raised Channel Catfish|journal=Transactions of the American Fisheries Society|volume=115|issue=3|pages=485\u2013489|doi=10.1577/1548-8659(1986)115<485:gamfip>2.0.co;2|issn=0002-8487}}</ref> Geosmin combines with [[2-methylisoborneol]], which concentrates in the fatty skin and dark muscle tissues. It breaks down in acid conditions; hence, vinegar and other acidic ingredients are used in fish recipes to reduce the muddy flavor.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3tKAfqxkFAIC|title=Westwood Lake Chronicles|last=Winkler|first=Lawrence|date=2012-08-06|publisher=Lawrence Winkler|isbn=9780991694105|language=en}}</ref> Taste and odor compounds including geosmin lead to an unpleasant taste of drinking water which is perceived by consumers as an indication of poor water quality.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Bristow | first1 = R.L. | last2 = Young | first2 = I.S. | last3 = Pemberton | first3 = A. | last4 = Williams | first4 = J. | last5 = Maher | first5 = S. | title = An extensive review of the extraction techniques and detection methods for the taste and odour compound geosmin (trans-1, 10-dimethyl-trans-9-decalol) in water | journal = Trends in Analytical Chemistry | volume = 110 | pages = 233\u2013248 | year = 2019 | doi = 10.1016/j.trac.2018.10.032 }}</ref>\n\nThis compound is also an issue for saltwater fish farmed in [[Recirculating aquaculture system|recirculating aquaculture systems]], such as Atlantic salmon.  These systems rely on biological filtration using cultured microbial communities to process the nitrogenous waste from the fish (ammonia) into less harmful compounds (nitrite and nitrate) that can be tolerated at higher concentrations.  However geosmin-producing bacteria can also grow in these systems, and often require fish to be transferred to an additional \"finishing\" or \"purge\" system where they are not fed for several days prior to harvest to remove off-flavor compounds and empty the intestinal tract. This process is also known as [[depuration]].\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Petrichor]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n\n* {{ cite journal | volume = 201 | issue = 4923 | pages = 993\u2013995 | last = Bear | first = I.J. |author2=R.G. Thomas | title = Nature of argillaceous odour | journal = [[Nature (journal)|Nature]] | year = 1964 | doi = 10.1038/201993a0 | bibcode = 1964Natur.201..993B }}\n* {{ cite journal | volume = 207 | issue = 5005 | pages = 1415\u20131416 | last = Bear | first = I.J. |author2=R.G. Thomas | title = Petrichor and plant growth | journal = [[Nature (journal)|Nature]] | year = 1965 | doi = 10.1038/2071415a0 | bibcode = 1965Natur.207.1415B }}\n\n[[Category:Tertiary alcohols]]\n[[Category:Flavors]]\n[[Category:Soil]]\n[[Category:Decalins]]\n[[Category:Foul-smelling chemicals]]\n", "text_old": "{{chembox\n| Watchedfields = changed\n| verifiedrevid = 447312555\n| Name = Geosmin\n| ImageFile = Geosmin Structural Formulae.svg\n| ImageSize = 150px\n| ImageName = Geosmin\n| IUPACName = (4''S'',4a''S'',8a''R'')-4,8a-dimethyloctahydronaphthalen-4a(2''H'')-ol\n| OtherNames = (4''S'',4a''S'',8a''R'')-4,8a-Dimethyl-1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8-octahydronaphthalen-4a-ol; 4,8a-Dimethyl-decahydronaphthalen-4a-ol; Octahydro-4,8a-dimethyl-4a(2''H'')-naphthalenol\n|Section1={{Chembox Identifiers\n| ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}}\n| ChemSpiderID = 27642\n| StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChI = 1S/C12H22O/c1-10-6-5-8-11(2)7-3-4-9-12(10,11)13/h10,13H,3-9H2,1-2H3/t10-,11+,12-/m0/s1\n| StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChIKey = JLPUXFOGCDVKGO-TUAOUCFPSA-N\n| CASNo_Ref = {{cascite|correct|??}}\n| CASNo = 19700-21-1\n| PubChem = 29746\n| ChEBI_Ref = {{ebicite|correct|EBI}}\n| ChEBI = 46702\n| SMILES = O[C@]12[C@H](CCC[C@]2(CCCC1)C)C\n| InChI = 1/C12H22O/c1-10-6-5-8-11(2)7-3-4-9-12(10,11)13/h10,13H,3-9H2,1-2H3\n/t10-,11+,12-/m0/s1\n  }}\n|Section2={{Chembox Properties\n| C=12|H=22|O=1\n| BoilingPtC = 270 to 271\n  }}\n|Section7={{Chembox Hazards\n| FlashPtC = 104\n  }}\n}}\n\n'''Geosmin''' is an [[organic compound]] with a distinct earthy flavor and aroma. This compound is responsible for the majority of taste and odor outbreaks in drinking water worldwide <ref>[https://aem.asm.org/content/73/14/4395/ Biochemical and Ecological Control of Geosmin\nand 2-Methylisoborneol in Source Waters], \"Applied and Environmental Microbiology\", Volume 73, July 2007.</ref>. Geosmin is also responsible for the earthy taste of [[beetroot]]s and a contributor to the strong scent ([[petrichor]]) that occurs in the air when rain falls after a dry spell of weather or when soil is disturbed.<ref>[http://www.expasy.org/spotlight/back_issues/035/ The earth's perfume], ''Protein Spotlight'', Issue 35, June 2003.</ref> \n\nIn chemical terms, it is a [[Bicyclic molecule|bicyclic]] [[alcohol]] with [[chemical formula|formula]] {{Chemical formula|C|12|H|22|O}}, a derivative of [[decalin]]. Its name is derived from the [[Ancient Greek]] {{lang|grc|[[wikt:\u03b3\u1fc6|\u03b3\u03b5\u03c9-]]}} {{transl|grc|ge\u014d-}} \"earth\" and {{lang|grc|[[wikt:\u1f40\u03c3\u03bc\u03ae|\u1f40\u03c3\u03bc\u03ae]]}} {{transl|grc|osm\u1e17}} \"smell\".  The word was coined in 1965 by the American biochemist Nancy N. Gerber (1929\u20131985) and the French-American biologist Hubert A. Lechevalier (1926\u20132015).<ref name=\"Gerber\" /><ref>[https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/geosmin Merriam-Webster dictionary:  geosmin ]</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n\nGeosmin is produced by various blue-green algae ([[cyanobacteria]]) and filamentous bacteria in the class [[Actinomyces]], and also some other prokaryotes and eukaryotes. The main genera in the cyanobacteria that have been shown to produce geosmin include ''[[Anabaena]]'', ''[[Phormidium]]'', and ''[[Planktothrix]]'', while the main genus in the Actinomyces that produces geosmin is ''[[Streptomyces]]''.  <ref>[https://aem.asm.org/content/73/14/4395/ Biochemical and Ecological Control of Geosmin\nand 2-Methylisoborneol in Source Waters], \"Applied and Environmental Microbiology\", Volume 73, July 2007.</ref>. <ref>{{cite journal | authors = Izaguirre G, Taylor WD. | year = 2004 | title = A guide to geosmin- and MIB-producing cyanobacteria in the United States | journal = Water Sci. Technol. | volume = 49 | issue = 9 | pages = 19\u201324 | pmid = 15237602| doi = 10.2166/wst.2004.0524 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | authors = Zaitlin B, Watson SB. | year = 2006 | title = Actinomycetes in relation to taste and odour in drinking water: Myths, tenets and truths | journal = Water Res. | volume = 40 | issue = 9 | pages = 1741\u201353 | pmid = 16600325 | doi = 10.1016/j.watres.2006.02.024}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | authors = Suurn\u00e4kki S, Gomez-Saez GV, Rantala-Ylinen A, Jokela J, Fewer DP, Sivonen K. | year = 2015 | title = Identification of geosmin and 2-methylisoborneol in cyanobacteria and molecular detection methods for the producers of these compounds | journal = Water Res. | volume = 68 | issue = 1 | pages = 56\u201366 | pmid = 25462716 | doi = 10.1016/j.watres.2014.09.037}}</ref> Communities whose [[water]] supplies depend on surface water can periodically experience episodes of unpleasant-tasting water when a sharp drop in the population of these bacteria releases geosmin into the local water supply. Under [[acid]]ic conditions, geosmin decomposes into odorless substances.<ref name = \"Gerber\">{{cite journal | pmid = 5866039 | volume=13 | issue=6 |date=November 1965 | pages=935\u20138 | last1 = Gerber | first1 = NN | last2 = Lechevalier | first2 = HA | title = Geosmin, an earthly-smelling substance isolated from actinomycetes. | pmc = 1058374 | journal = Applied Microbiology}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, the [[biosynthesis]] of geosmin by a bifunctional ''[[Streptomyces coelicolor]]'' [[enzyme]] was unveiled.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1021/ja062669x | volume = 128 | issue = 25 | pages = 8128\u20138129 | last1 = Jiang | first1 = J. | first2 = X. | last2 = He | first3 = D.E. | last3 = Cane | title = Geosmin biosynthesis. ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' germacradienol/germacrene D Synthase converts farnesyl diphosphate to geosmin | journal = [[J. Am. Chem. Soc.]] | year = 2006 | pmid = 16787064}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1038/nchembio.2007.29 | volume = 3| last1 = Jiang | first1 = J. | first2 = X. | last2 = He | first3 = D.E. | last3 = Cane | pmc = 3013058 | title = Biosynthesis of the earthy odorant geosmin by a bifunctional ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' enzyme | journal = [[Nat. Chem. Biol.]] | year = 2007 | pages = 711\u20135 | pmid = 17873868 | issue = 11}}</ref> A single enzyme, [[geosmin synthase]], converts [[farnesyl diphosphate]] to geosmin in a two-step reaction.\n\n''Streptomyces coelicolor'' is the model representative of a group of soil-dwelling bacteria with a complex lifecycle involving [[Mycelium|mycelial growth]] and [[spore formation]]. Besides the production of volatile geosmin, it also produces many other complex molecules of pharmacological interest; its [[genome]] sequence is available at the [[Sanger Institute]].<ref name=\"Sanger\">{{cite web |title=The genome of ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' A3(2) producing geosmin |publisher=Sanger Institute |url=http://www.sanger.ac.uk/Projects/S_coelicolor/ |accessdate=2009-01-31}}</ref>\n\n== Effects ==\n\nThe [[human nose]] is extremely sensitive to geosmin and is able to detect it at concentrations as low as 5 parts per trillion.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Polak | first1 = E.H. | last2 = Provasi | first2 = J. | title = Odor sensitivity to geosmin enantiomers | journal = Chemical Senses | volume = 17 | pages = 23\u201326 | year = 1992 | doi = 10.1093/chemse/17.1.23 }}</ref>\n\nGeosmin is responsible for the muddy smell in many commercially important freshwater fish such as [[carp]] and [[catfish]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Vallod|first=D.|last2=Cravedi|first2=J. P.|last3=Hillenweck|first3=A.|last4=Robin|first4=J.|date=2007-04-03|title=Analysis of the off-flavor risk in carp production in ponds in Dombes and Forez (France)|journal=Aquaculture International|language=en|volume=15|issue=3\u20134|pages=287\u2013298|doi=10.1007/s10499-007-9080-7|issn=0967-6120}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lovell|first=Richard T.|last2=Lelana|first2=Iwan Y.|last3=Boyd|first3=Claude E.|last4=Armstrong|first4=Martin S.|date=1986-05-01|title=Geosmin and Musty-Muddy Flavors in Pond-Raised Channel Catfish|journal=Transactions of the American Fisheries Society|volume=115|issue=3|pages=485\u2013489|doi=10.1577/1548-8659(1986)115<485:gamfip>2.0.co;2|issn=0002-8487}}</ref> Geosmin combines with [[2-methylisoborneol]], which concentrates in the fatty skin and dark muscle tissues. It breaks down in acid conditions; hence, vinegar and other acidic ingredients are used in fish recipes to reduce the muddy flavor.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3tKAfqxkFAIC|title=Westwood Lake Chronicles|last=Winkler|first=Lawrence|date=2012-08-06|publisher=Lawrence Winkler|isbn=9780991694105|language=en}}</ref> Taste and odor compounds including geosmin lead to an unpleasant taste of drinking water which is perceived by consumers as an indication of poor water quality.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Bristow | first1 = R.L. | last2 = Young | first2 = I.S. | last3 = Pemberton | first3 = A. | last4 = Williams | first4 = J. | last5 = Maher | first5 = S. | title = An extensive review of the extraction techniques and detection methods for the taste and odour compound geosmin (trans-1, 10-dimethyl-trans-9-decalol) in water | journal = Trends in Analytical Chemistry | volume = 110 | pages = 233\u2013248 | year = 2019 | doi = 10.1016/j.trac.2018.10.032 }}</ref>\n\nThis compound is also an issue for saltwater fish farmed in [[Recirculating aquaculture system|recirculating aquaculture systems]], such as Atlantic salmon.  These systems rely on biological filtration using cultured microbial communities to process the nitrogenous waste from the fish (ammonia) into less harmful compounds (nitrite and nitrate) that can be tolerated at higher concentrations.  However geosmin-producing bacteria can also grow in these systems, and often require fish to be transferred to an additional \"finishing\" or \"purge\" system where they are not fed for several days prior to harvest to remove off-flavor compounds and empty the intestinal tract. This process is also known as [[depuration]].\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Petrichor]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n\n* {{ cite journal | volume = 201 | issue = 4923 | pages = 993\u2013995 | last = Bear | first = I.J. |author2=R.G. Thomas | title = Nature of argillaceous odour | journal = [[Nature (journal)|Nature]] | year = 1964 | doi = 10.1038/201993a0 | bibcode = 1964Natur.201..993B }}\n* {{ cite journal | volume = 207 | issue = 5005 | pages = 1415\u20131416 | last = Bear | first = I.J. |author2=R.G. Thomas | title = Petrichor and plant growth | journal = [[Nature (journal)|Nature]] | year = 1965 | doi = 10.1038/2071415a0 | bibcode = 1965Natur.207.1415B }}\n\n[[Category:Tertiary alcohols]]\n[[Category:Flavors]]\n[[Category:Soil]]\n[[Category:Decalins]]\n[[Category:Foul-smelling chemicals]]\n", "name_user": "Zaitlin241", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geosmin"}
{"title_page": "Sell your cloak and buy a sword", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Undue weight|to=fringe 'Christian anarchist' or 'Christian pacifist' interpretations of this biblical passage|date=July 2018}}\n{{Overquotation|date=August 2019}}\n}}\n'''Sell your cloak and buy a sword''' is an instruction, by [[Jesus]] to his [[Disciple (Christianity)|disciples]] during the [[Last Supper]],<ref>Luke 22:36, NIV</ref> which has been interpreted in several ways.\n\n==Interpretation==\n===Fulfillment of prophecy interpretation===\nThis means, to overcome the anti spirit in your midst who came and stayed in your heart by his wine because The Word has allowed the breach.  \"I would have you purchase from Me, pure Gold.\" Receive the true S.O.P. \nSpirit\nOf \nProphecy (The Prophet; Teacher)\nForsake the fake SOP\nSON\nOF \nPERDITION\nSIMON\nPETER (FALSE PROPHET)\n[[Christian anarchist]] [[Jacques Ellul]] and [[Christian pacifist]] [[John Howard Yoder]] do not believe Luke 22:36 overturns the many times Jesus urged his followers to [[turning the other cheek|turn the other cheek]] and [[Matthew 5:39|not resist evil]] when confronted by violence during his [[Sermon on the Mount]] and [[Ministry of Jesus|years of ministry]]. They show when the passage is taken in context (Luke 22:36-38), Jesus is also aware of fulfilling prophecy and makes a surprising statement that two swords are \"enough.\"<ref \nname=Christoyannopoulos>{{cite book |title=Christian Anarchism: A Political Commentary on the Gospel |last=Christoyannopoulos |first=Alexandre |authorlink=Alexandre Christoyannopoulos |coauthors= |year=2010 |publisher=Imprint Academic |location=Exeter |isbn= |page= |pages=109\u2013110 |url= |accessdate= |quote=Two swords could not possibly have been 'enough' to defend Jesus from his pending arrest, trial and execution, so their sole purpose must have been Jesus' wish to fulfill a prophecy}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|He said to them, \u201cBut now if you have a purse, take it, and also a bag; and if you don\u2019t have a sword, sell your cloak and buy one. It is written: \u2018And he was numbered with the transgressors\u2019; and I tell you that this must be fulfilled in me. Yes, what is written about me is reaching its fulfillment.\u201d The disciples said, \u201cSee, Lord, here are two swords.\u201d \u201cThat\u2019s enough!\u201d he replied.|[[Gospel of Luke]] 22:36-38, NIV }}\n\nEllul, Yoder and [[Archie Penner]] claim that two swords could not possibly have been \"enough\" to defend Jesus from his pending arrest, trial and execution, so their sole purpose must have been Jesus' wish to fulfill a prophecy (Isaiah 53:9-12).<ref name=Christoyannopoulos /> As Ellul explains:\n{{quote|The further comment of Jesus explains in part the surprising statement, for he says: \"It is necessary that the prophecy be fulfilled according to which I would be put in the ranks of criminals\" (Luke 22:36-37). The idea of fighting with just two swords is ridiculous. The swords are enough, however, to justify the accusation that Jesus is the head of a band of brigands. We have to note here that Jesus is consciously fulfilling prophecy. If he were not the saying would make no sense.<ref>{{cite book |title=Anarchy and Christianity |last=Ellul |first=Jacques |authorlink=Jacques Ellul |coauthors= |year=1988 |publisher= |location= |isbn= |page=64 |pages= |url= |accessdate= |quote=The further comment of Jesus explains in part the surprising statement, for he says: 'It is necessary that the prophecy be fulfilled according to which I would be put in the ranks of criminals' (Luke 22:36-37). The idea of fighting with just two swords is ridiculous. The swords are enough, however, to justify the accusation that Jesus is the head of a band of brigands. We have to note here that Jesus is consciously fulfilling prophecy. If he were not the saying would make no sense}}</ref>}}\n\nThis theory is further substantiated by [[Saint Peter|Peter]] when Peter draws one of the swords a few hours later at [[Arrest of Jesus|Jesus' arrest]] in the [[Garden of Gethsemane]], slashing the ear of [[Malchus]], one of the [[Kohen|priest]]s' servants, and Jesus rebukes him saying: \"Put up again thy sword into his place: for all they that [[Live by the sword, die by the sword|take the sword shall perish with the sword]].\"(Matthew 26:52)<ref name=Christoyannopoulos />\n\n[[Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary|Jamieson, Fausset and Brown]], in their 1871 biblical commentary, indicate \"...And He said to them, It is enough - not 'Two swords will suffice,' but 'Enough of this for the present'. The warning had been given, and preparation for coming dangers hinted at; but as His meaning had not been apprehended in the comprehensive sense in which it was meant, He wished to leave the subject\".<ref>Robert Jamieson, A.R.Faussett and David Brown ''A Commentary, Critical, Experimental, and Practical on the Old and New Testaments Volume 3, Part One.'' William B. Erdsmans Publishing Company, Grand Rapids Michigan, reprinted 1976, p.329 notes pertaining to Luke 22 vss 35 and 36</ref>\n\nMotyer, Stibbs and Wiseman in New Bible Commentary: Revised Third Edition (1977) states:\n{{quote|\n35-38- Finally, Jesus spoke of the new situation. Formerly, when the Disciples had gone out, on mission, they had not lacked anything. Now they would need a purse, a bag and even a sword. The saying is heavily ironical, for Jesus knew that now He would have to face universal opposition and be put to death. But the disciples misunderstood Him and produced weapons. 'That is enough', said Jesus to end a conversation which they had failed to understand. The way of Jesus, as they should have known, was not the way of the sword, but of love.<ref>D.Guthrie, J.A. Motyer, A.M. Stibbs, D.J Wiseman, ''The New Bible Commentary: Revised Third Edition'' Guideposts, Carmel New York. p 921 in reference to Luke 22:35-38</ref>}}\n\n===Figurative===\nPope [[Boniface VIII]] referred to the two swords in the medieval papal bull ''[[Unam sanctam]]'', to represent the temporal and spiritual authority of the church. He wrote: \"We are informed by the texts of the gospels that in this Church and in its power are two swords; namely, the spiritual and the temporal. For when the Apostles say: \"Behold, here are two swords\" [Lk 22:38] that is to say, in the Church, since the Apostles were speaking, the Lord did not reply that there were too many, but sufficient.\"<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/library/docs_bo08us.htm Unam Sanctam, His Holiness Pope Boniface VIII: November 18, 1302] </ref>\n\nTheologian [[John Gill (theologian)|John Gill]] said in his ''Exposition of the Entire Bible'':\n{{quote|These words of Christ are not to be understood literally, that he would have his disciples furnish themselves with swords at any rate, since he would never have said, as he afterwards does, that two were sufficient; which could not be enough for eleven men; or have forbid Peter the use of one, as he did in a very little time after this: but his meaning is, that wherever they came, and a door was opened for the preaching of the Gospel, they would have many adversaries, and these powerful, and would be used with great violence, and be followed with rage and persecution; so that they might seem to stand in need of swords to defend them: the phrase is expressive of the danger they would be exposed to, and of their need of protection; and therefore it was wrong in them to be disputing and quarrelling about superiority, or looking out for, and expecting temporal pomp and grandeur, when this would be their forlorn, destitute, and afflicted condition; and they would quickly see the affliction and distress begin in himself. In \"seven\" ancient copies of [[Beza]]'s, it is read in the future tense, \"he shall take, he shall sell, he shall buy\".}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Not peace, but a sword]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Christian terminology]]\n[[Category:Gospel of Luke]]\n[[Category:New Testament words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Sayings of Jesus]]\n[[Category:Swords]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Undue weight|to=fringe 'Christian anarchist' or 'Christian pacifist' interpretations of this biblical passage|date=July 2018}}\n{{Overquotation|date=August 2019}}\n}}\n'''Sell your cloak and buy a sword''' is an instruction, by [[Jesus]] to his [[Disciple (Christianity)|disciples]] during the [[Last Supper]],<ref>Luke 22:36, NIV</ref> which has been interpreted in several ways.\n\n==Interpretation==\n===Fulfillment of prophecy interpretation===\n[[Christian anarchist]] [[Jacques Ellul]] and [[Christian pacifist]] [[John Howard Yoder]] do not believe Luke 22:36 overturns the many times Jesus urged his followers to [[turning the other cheek|turn the other cheek]] and [[Matthew 5:39|not resist evil]] when confronted by violence during his [[Sermon on the Mount]] and [[Ministry of Jesus|years of ministry]]. They show when the passage is taken in context (Luke 22:36-38), Jesus is also aware of fulfilling prophecy and makes a surprising statement that two swords are \"enough.\"<ref \nname=Christoyannopoulos>{{cite book |title=Christian Anarchism: A Political Commentary on the Gospel |last=Christoyannopoulos |first=Alexandre |authorlink=Alexandre Christoyannopoulos |coauthors= |year=2010 |publisher=Imprint Academic |location=Exeter |isbn= |page= |pages=109\u2013110 |url= |accessdate= |quote=Two swords could not possibly have been 'enough' to defend Jesus from his pending arrest, trial and execution, so their sole purpose must have been Jesus' wish to fulfill a prophecy}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|He said to them, \u201cBut now if you have a purse, take it, and also a bag; and if you don\u2019t have a sword, sell your cloak and buy one. It is written: \u2018And he was numbered with the transgressors\u2019; and I tell you that this must be fulfilled in me. Yes, what is written about me is reaching its fulfillment.\u201d The disciples said, \u201cSee, Lord, here are two swords.\u201d \u201cThat\u2019s enough!\u201d he replied.|[[Gospel of Luke]] 22:36-38, NIV }}\n\nEllul, Yoder and [[Archie Penner]] claim that two swords could not possibly have been \"enough\" to defend Jesus from his pending arrest, trial and execution, so their sole purpose must have been Jesus' wish to fulfill a prophecy (Isaiah 53:9-12).<ref name=Christoyannopoulos /> As Ellul explains:\n{{quote|The further comment of Jesus explains in part the surprising statement, for he says: \"It is necessary that the prophecy be fulfilled according to which I would be put in the ranks of criminals\" (Luke 22:36-37). The idea of fighting with just two swords is ridiculous. The swords are enough, however, to justify the accusation that Jesus is the head of a band of brigands. We have to note here that Jesus is consciously fulfilling prophecy. If he were not the saying would make no sense.<ref>{{cite book |title=Anarchy and Christianity |last=Ellul |first=Jacques |authorlink=Jacques Ellul |coauthors= |year=1988 |publisher= |location= |isbn= |page=64 |pages= |url= |accessdate= |quote=The further comment of Jesus explains in part the surprising statement, for he says: 'It is necessary that the prophecy be fulfilled according to which I would be put in the ranks of criminals' (Luke 22:36-37). The idea of fighting with just two swords is ridiculous. The swords are enough, however, to justify the accusation that Jesus is the head of a band of brigands. We have to note here that Jesus is consciously fulfilling prophecy. If he were not the saying would make no sense}}</ref>}}\n\nThis theory is further substantiated by [[Saint Peter|Peter]] when Peter draws one of the swords a few hours later at [[Arrest of Jesus|Jesus' arrest]] in the [[Garden of Gethsemane]], slashing the ear of [[Malchus]], one of the [[Kohen|priest]]s' servants, and Jesus rebukes him saying: \"Put up again thy sword into his place: for all they that [[Live by the sword, die by the sword|take the sword shall perish with the sword]].\"(Matthew 26:52)<ref name=Christoyannopoulos />\n\n[[Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary|Jamieson, Fausset and Brown]], in their 1871 biblical commentary, indicate \"...And He said to them, It is enough - not 'Two swords will suffice,' but 'Enough of this for the present'. The warning had been given, and preparation for coming dangers hinted at; but as His meaning had not been apprehended in the comprehensive sense in which it was meant, He wished to leave the subject\".<ref>Robert Jamieson, A.R.Faussett and David Brown ''A Commentary, Critical, Experimental, and Practical on the Old and New Testaments Volume 3, Part One.'' William B. Erdsmans Publishing Company, Grand Rapids Michigan, reprinted 1976, p.329 notes pertaining to Luke 22 vss 35 and 36</ref>\n\nMotyer, Stibbs and Wiseman in New Bible Commentary: Revised Third Edition (1977) states:\n{{quote|\n35-38- Finally, Jesus spoke of the new situation. Formerly, when the Disciples had gone out, on mission, they had not lacked anything. Now they would need a purse, a bag and even a sword. The saying is heavily ironical, for Jesus knew that now He would have to face universal opposition and be put to death. But the disciples misunderstood Him and produced weapons. 'That is enough', said Jesus to end a conversation which they had failed to understand. The way of Jesus, as they should have known, was not the way of the sword, but of love.<ref>D.Guthrie, J.A. Motyer, A.M. Stibbs, D.J Wiseman, ''The New Bible Commentary: Revised Third Edition'' Guideposts, Carmel New York. p 921 in reference to Luke 22:35-38</ref>}}\n\n===Figurative===\nPope [[Boniface VIII]] referred to the two swords in the medieval papal bull ''[[Unam sanctam]]'', to represent the temporal and spiritual authority of the church. He wrote: \"We are informed by the texts of the gospels that in this Church and in its power are two swords; namely, the spiritual and the temporal. For when the Apostles say: \"Behold, here are two swords\" [Lk 22:38] that is to say, in the Church, since the Apostles were speaking, the Lord did not reply that there were too many, but sufficient.\"<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/library/docs_bo08us.htm Unam Sanctam, His Holiness Pope Boniface VIII: November 18, 1302] </ref>\n\nTheologian [[John Gill (theologian)|John Gill]] said in his ''Exposition of the Entire Bible'':\n{{quote|These words of Christ are not to be understood literally, that he would have his disciples furnish themselves with swords at any rate, since he would never have said, as he afterwards does, that two were sufficient; which could not be enough for eleven men; or have forbid Peter the use of one, as he did in a very little time after this: but his meaning is, that wherever they came, and a door was opened for the preaching of the Gospel, they would have many adversaries, and these powerful, and would be used with great violence, and be followed with rage and persecution; so that they might seem to stand in need of swords to defend them: the phrase is expressive of the danger they would be exposed to, and of their need of protection; and therefore it was wrong in them to be disputing and quarrelling about superiority, or looking out for, and expecting temporal pomp and grandeur, when this would be their forlorn, destitute, and afflicted condition; and they would quickly see the affliction and distress begin in himself. In \"seven\" ancient copies of [[Beza]]'s, it is read in the future tense, \"he shall take, he shall sell, he shall buy\".}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Not peace, but a sword]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Christian terminology]]\n[[Category:Gospel of Luke]]\n[[Category:New Testament words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Sayings of Jesus]]\n[[Category:Swords]]\n", "name_user": "47.219.193.23", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eFulfillment of prophecy interpretation:Gave the true Instruction from Jesus)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sell_your_cloak_and_buy_a_sword"}
{"title_page": "Tatul Hakobyan", "text_new": "__NOTOC__\n[[File:Tatul Hakobyan.jpg|thumb|Hakobyan in 2018]]\n\n'''Tatul Hakobyan''' ({{lang-hy|\u0539\u0561\u0569\u0578\u0582\u056c \u0540\u0561\u056f\u0578\u0562\u0575\u0561\u0576}}; born December 29, 1969) is an [[Armenians|Armenian]] reporter and an independent political analyst.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Guliyev|first1=Emil|last2=Harutyunyan|first2=Mariam|title=Russia's Crimea move could reignite Karabakh conflict: analysts|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/russias-crimea-move-could-reignite-karabakh-conflict-analysts-195212366.html|agency=[[Yahoo! News]]|date=7 May 2014|quote=Tatul Hakobyan, an independent analyst in Yerevan.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Displacement and Status in the Nagorno Karabakh Conflict|url=https://www.chathamhouse.org/sites/files/chathamhouse/public/Research/Russia%20and%20Eurasia/211112summary.pdf|publisher=[[Chatham House]]|page=2|date=21 November 2012|quote=Tatul Hakobyan (Reporter and Analyst, Civilitas Foundation, Armenia)}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nHakobyan was born in the village of [[Dovegh]] in northeastern Armenia, near the hostile border with [[Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sargsyan|first1=Voskan|title=\u0539\u0561\u0569\u0578\u0582\u056c \u0540\u0561\u056f\u0578\u0562\u0575\u0561\u0576. \"\u0535\u0569\u0565 \u0563\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0572\u0561\u0581\u056b\u0576 \u0574\u0578\u056c\u0578\u0580\u057e\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0567, \u0561\u057a\u0561 \u056f\u0561\u0580\u0578\u0572 \u0567 \"\u0574\u0578\u056c\u0578\u0580\u057e\u0565\u056c\" \u0576\u0561\u0565\u0582 \u0561\u0564\u0580\u0562\u0565\u057b\u0561\u0576\u0581\u056b \u0564\u056b\u057e\u0565\u0580\u057d\u0561\u0576\u057f\u0568\"|url=http://www.aravot.am/2014/08/11/487675/|work=[[Aravot]]|language=hy|quote=\u0546\u0578\u0575\u0565\u0574\u0562\u0565\u0580\u0575\u0561\u0576\u056b \u057d\u0561\u0570\u0574\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0574\u0565\u0580\u0571 \u0534\u0578\u057e\u0565\u0572 \u0563\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0572\u056b\u0581 \u057d\u0565\u0580\u057e\u0561\u056e \u0539\u0561\u0569\u0578\u0582\u056c \u0540\u0561\u056f\u0578\u0562\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568...}}</ref> He attended the [[Yerevan State University]] and graduated from the Journalism Department in 1995.<ref name=\"ypc\"/>\n\n==Career==\nHakobyan has formerly worked as a correspondent for the newspapers ''[[Yerkir]]'' (1998-2000), ''[[Azg (daily)|Azg]]'' (2000-06), ''[[Aztag (daily)|Aztag]]'' (since 2005),<ref name=\"hetq\"/> ''[[The Armenian Reporter]]'' (2008-9) and as a political observer on regional issues of ''Radiolur'' news program of [[Public Radio of Armenia]] (2004\u201308). Since 2009 he has been a reporter and an analyst at the independent [[Civilitas Foundation]].<ref name=\"ypc\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Grigoryan|first1=Marianna|title=Armenia: Yerevan Growing More Cautious on Reconciliation with Turkey|url=http://www.eurasianet.org/departments/insight/articles/eav010610.shtml|work=[[EurasiaNet]]|date=5 January 2010|quote=Tatul Hakobyan, an analyst at the Civilitas Foundation...}}</ref>\n\nHakobyan has been the director of the Yerevan-based ANI Foundation for Armenian Studies (\u0540\u0561\u0575\u056f\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576 \u0578\u0582\u057d\u0578\u0582\u0574\u0576\u0561\u057d\u056b\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0576\u0565\u0580\u056b \u0531\u0546\u053b \u0570\u056b\u0574\u0576\u0561\u0564\u0580\u0561\u0574).<ref name=\"hetq\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aniarc.am/|title=aniarc.am - \u0540\u0531\u0545\u053f\u0531\u053f\u0531\u0546 \u0548\u0552\u054d\u0548\u0552\u0544\u0546\u0531\u054d\u053b\u0550\u0548\u0552\u0539\u0545\u0548\u0552\u0546\u0546\u0535\u0550\u053b \u0531\u0546\u053b \u0540\u053b\u0544\u0546\u0531\u0534\u0550\u0531\u0544|author=\u0539\u0531\u0539\u0548\u0552\u053c \u0540\u0531\u053f\u0548\u0532\u0545\u0531\u0546|work=aniarc.am|accessdate=3 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHakobyan is married with two sons. He speaks Armenian, Russian, English, and Spanish.<ref name=\"ypc\"/>\n\n==Publications==\n*\u053f\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0579 \u0578\u0582 \u057d\u0587. \u0561\u0580\u0581\u0561\u056d\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u0585\u0580\u0561\u0563\u056b\u0580 [Green and black: Karabakh diary] (2008)\n*\u0540\u0561\u0575\u0561\u0581\u0584 \u0531\u0580\u0561\u0580\u0561\u057f\u056b\u0581. \u0570\u0561\u0575\u0565\u0580\u0568 \u0587 \u0569\u0578\u0582\u0580\u0584\u0565\u0580\u0568 [View from Ararat: Armenians and Turks] (2012)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"ypc\">{{cite web|title=HAKOBYAN Tatul|url=http://ypc.am/oldypc/whoiswho/ln/en/p/43915|website=ypc.am|publisher=Yerevan Press Club}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hetq\">{{cite news|title=Journalist Tatul Hakobyan to Head Newly Formed ANI Foundation for Armenian Studies|url=http://hetq.am/eng/news/58002/journalist-tatul-hakobyan-to-head-newly-formed-ani-foundation-for-armenian-studies.html|work=[[Hetq]]|date=2 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hakobyan, Tatul}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Armenian male writers]]\n[[Category:Armenian journalists]]\n[[Category:Yerevan State University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "__NOTOC__\n[[File:Tatul Hakobyan.jpg|thumb|Hakobyan in 2018]]\n\n'''Tatul Hakobyan''' ({{lang-hy|\u0539\u0561\u0569\u0578\u0582\u056c \u0540\u0561\u056f\u0578\u0562\u0575\u0561\u0576}}; born December 29, 1969) is an [[Armenians|Armenian]] reporter and an independent political analyst.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Guliyev|first1=Emil|last2=Harutyunyan|first2=Mariam|title=Russia's Crimea move could reignite Karabakh conflict: analysts|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/russias-crimea-move-could-reignite-karabakh-conflict-analysts-195212366.html|agency=[[Yahoo! News]]|date=7 May 2014|quote=Tatul Hakobyan, an independent analyst in Yerevan.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Displacement and Status in the Nagorno Karabakh Conflict|url=https://www.chathamhouse.org/sites/files/chathamhouse/public/Research/Russia%20and%20Eurasia/211112summary.pdf|publisher=[[Chatham House]]|page=2|date=21 November 2012|quote=Tatul Hakobyan (Reporter and Analyst, Civilitas Foundation, Armenia)}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nHakobyan was born in the village of [[Dovegh]] in northeastern Armenia, near the hostile border with [[Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sargsyan|first1=Voskan|title=\u0539\u0561\u0569\u0578\u0582\u056c \u0540\u0561\u056f\u0578\u0562\u0575\u0561\u0576. \"\u0535\u0569\u0565 \u0563\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0572\u0561\u0581\u056b\u0576 \u0574\u0578\u056c\u0578\u0580\u057e\u0578\u0582\u0574 \u0567, \u0561\u057a\u0561 \u056f\u0561\u0580\u0578\u0572 \u0567 \"\u0574\u0578\u056c\u0578\u0580\u057e\u0565\u056c\" \u0576\u0561\u0565\u0582 \u0561\u0564\u0580\u0562\u0565\u057b\u0561\u0576\u0581\u056b \u0564\u056b\u057e\u0565\u0580\u057d\u0561\u0576\u057f\u0568\"|url=http://www.aravot.am/2014/08/11/487675/|work=[[Aravot]]|language=hy|quote=\u0546\u0578\u0575\u0565\u0574\u0562\u0565\u0580\u0575\u0561\u0576\u056b \u057d\u0561\u0570\u0574\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0574\u0565\u0580\u0571 \u0534\u0578\u057e\u0565\u0572 \u0563\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0572\u056b\u0581 \u057d\u0565\u0580\u057e\u0561\u056e \u0539\u0561\u0569\u0578\u0582\u056c \u0540\u0561\u056f\u0578\u0562\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568...}}</ref> He attended the [[Yerevan State University]] and graduated from the Journalism Department in 1995.<ref name=\"ypc\"/>\n\n==Career==\nHakobyan has formerly worked as a correspondent for the newspapers ''[[Yerkir]]'' (1998-2000), ''[[Azg (daily)|Azg]]'' (2000-06), ''[[Aztag (daily)|Aztag]]'' (since 2005),<ref name=\"hetq\"/> ''[[The Armenian Reporter]]'' (2008-9) and as a political observer on regional issues of ''Radiolur'' news program of [[Public Radio of Armenia]] (2004\u201308). Since 2009 he has been a reporter and an analyst at the independent [[Civilitas Foundation]].<ref name=\"ypc\"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Grigoryan|first1=Marianna|title=Armenia: Yerevan Growing More Cautious on Reconciliation with Turkey|url=http://www.eurasianet.org/departments/insight/articles/eav010610.shtml|work=[[EurasiaNet]]|date=5 January 2010|quote=Tatul Hakobyan, an analyst at the Civilitas Foundation...}}</ref>\n\nHakobyan has been the director of the Yerevan-based ANI Foundation for Armenian Studies (\u0540\u0561\u0575\u056f\u0561\u056f\u0561\u0576 \u0578\u0582\u057d\u0578\u0582\u0574\u0576\u0561\u057d\u056b\u0580\u0578\u0582\u0569\u0575\u0578\u0582\u0576\u0576\u0565\u0580\u056b \u0531\u0546\u053b \u0570\u056b\u0574\u0576\u0561\u0564\u0580\u0561\u0574).<ref name=\"hetq\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aniarc.am/|title=aniarc.am - \u0540\u0531\u0545\u053f\u0531\u053f\u0531\u0546 \u0548\u0552\u054d\u0548\u0552\u0544\u0546\u0531\u054d\u053b\u0550\u0548\u0552\u0539\u0545\u0548\u0552\u0546\u0546\u0535\u0550\u053b \u0531\u0546\u053b \u0540\u053b\u0544\u0546\u0531\u0534\u0550\u0531\u0544|author=\u0539\u0531\u0539\u0548\u0552\u053c \u0540\u0531\u053f\u0548\u0532\u0545\u0531\u0546|work=aniarc.am|accessdate=3 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHakobyan is married with two sons. He speaks Armenian, Russian, English, and Spanish.<ref name=\"ypc\"/>\n\n==Publications==\n*\u053f\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0579 \u0578\u0582 \u057d\u0587. \u0561\u0580\u0581\u0561\u056d\u0575\u0561\u0576 \u0585\u0580\u0561\u0563\u056b\u0580 [Green and black: Karabakh diary] (2008)\n*\u0540\u0561\u0575\u0561\u0581\u0584 \u0531\u0580\u0561\u0580\u0561\u057f\u056b\u0581. \u0570\u0561\u0575\u0565\u0580\u0568 \u0587 \u0569\u0578\u0582\u0580\u0584\u0565\u0580\u0568 [View from Ararat: Armenians and Turks] (2012)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"ypc\">{{cite web|title=HAKOBYAN Tatul|url=http://ypc.am/oldypc/whoiswho/ln/en/p/43915|website=ypc.am|publisher=Yerevan Press Club}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hetq\">{{cite news|title=Journalist Tatul Hakobyan to Head Newly Formed ANI Foundation for Armenian Studies|url=http://hetq.am/eng/news/58002/journalist-tatul-hakobyan-to-head-newly-formed-ani-foundation-for-armenian-studies.html|work=[[Hetq]]|date=2 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hakobyan, Tatul}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Armenian male writers]]\n[[Category:Armenian journalists]]\n[[Category:Yerevan State University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tatul_Hakobyan"}
{"title_page": "Manspreading", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Practice of sitting in public transport with legs wide apart}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n[[File:Manspreading on Stockholm Metro.jpg|thumb|An example of \"manspreading\" on the [[Stockholm metro]]]]\n'''Manspreading''' or '''man-sitting''' is the practice of men sitting in public transport with legs wide apart, thereby covering more than one seat.<ref name=\"nytsimmons\">{{Cite news |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/21/nyregion/MTA-targets-manspreading-on-new-york-city-subways.html |title = A Scourge Is Spreading. M.T.A.\u2019s Cure? Dude, Close Your Legs. |last = Fitzsimmons |first = Emma G. |date = 20 December 2014 |work =The New York Times | access-date = }}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />. The public debate began when an anti-manspreading campaign started on the [[social media]] website [[Tumblr]] in 2013; the term appeared a year later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.oxforddictionaries.com/2015/09/manspreading-term-popularized-by-mta/|title=Manspreading: how New York City\u2019s MTA popularized a word without actually saying it|author=Katherine Connor Martin|year=2015|publisher=Oxford Dictionaries|accessdate=2016-07-12}}</ref> The journalist Babara Ellen described it in 2013 as \"essentially anger at the space these men feel entitled to take up\". <ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/sep/22/men-legs-splayed-on-train|title=Ellen, Barbara. The real reason men should keep their legs together. The Guardian, Sept 22, 213|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> [[OxfordDictionaries.com]] added the word \"manspreading\" in August 2015.<ref name=\"reuters\">{{Cite news |url = https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/27/us-life-manspread-idUSKCN0QW1Y620150827 |title = Manspreading, hangry, Grexit join Oxford online dictionary |date = 27 August 2015 |work = | access-date = | publisher = Reuters}}\n</ref><ref>\n{{cite web\n|title= New words in oxforddictionaries\n|url= https://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/aug/27/hangry-bants-fatberg-new-words-in-oxforddictionaries\n|accessdate= 28 August 2015\n}}\n</ref>. Manspreading is considered a form of  [[Microaggression]] against women because it is a way of disrespect to their personal space.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewaywomenwork.com/2019/04/5-examples-of-microaggressions-in-the-workplace/|title=Rania H. Anderson, 5 Examples of Microaggressions in the Workplace. Retrieved April 14, 2020|last=https://thewaywomenwork.com/2019/04/5-examples-of-microaggressions-in-the-workplace/|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>. Lyndsay Kirkham, a professor of English at Humber College, called man spreading a metaphor for men being given permission to take up more space in society.<ref name=\"TorontoSun\" />  \n\n==Transit authority responses==\n[[File:EMT Madrid ampl\u00eda su se\u00f1alizaci\u00f3n a bordo del autob\u00fas para evitar el \u201cmanspreading\u201d (01).jpg|thumb|Campaign encouraging respectful posture by [[Empresa Municipal de Transportes de Madrid|Madrid Municipal Transport Company]] in 2017.]]\nIn 2014 the [[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]] (MTA) in the [[New York metropolitan area]] and [[Sound Transit]] of [[Seattle]] instituted poster campaigns encouraging respectful posture when other passengers have to stand due to crowding on buses and trains. The MTA campaign, which criticized many behaviors such as leaning on poles and applying make-up, used the slogan \"Dude, stop the spread please!\"<ref>{{Cite news|last=Tahseen|first=Ismat|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/Mumbais-got-its-own-man-spreaders/articleshow/45609512.cms|title=Mumbai\u2019s got its own 'man-spreaders'|date=23 December 2014|work=The Times of India|access-date=|publisher=}}</ref> . Transport officials in [[Philadelphia]], [[Chicago]] and [[Washington D.C.]] have not noted complaints against manspreading in particular although the [[Philadelphia transportation authority|Philadelphia Transportation Authority]] at that time had an etiquete campaign with the slogan \u201cDude It\u2019s Rude... Two Seats \u2014 Really?\u201d aimed at people who occupied sits with bags. .<ref name=\"nytsimmons\" /> Despite social media pressure and public debate to extend the campaign to the Canadian city of [[Toronto]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://toronto.ctvnews.ca/movement-to-ban-man-spreading-on-transit-picks-up-speed-in-toronto-1.2158517|title=Movement to ban 'man-spreading' on transit picks up speed in Toronto, CTV Toronto\nPublished Monday, December 22, 2014|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/lifestyle/man-spreading-debate-spreads-to-toronto-1.2165494|title=Jesse Tahirali, 'Man-spreading' debate spreads to Toronto. CTV News. Published Monday, December 29, 2014|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>  a representative of the [[Toronto Transit Commission]] stated \u201cWe\u2019re not commenting on the manspreading campaign\", and she reminded the users to be courteous to each other. Allowing someone else to take an empty seat beside them.<ref name = \"TorontoSun\">{{cite news|last1=Yuen|first1=Jenny|title=Anti-'manspreading' campaign called sexist|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2014/12/29/anti-manspreading-campaign-called-sexist|accessdate=5 December 2015|publisher=The Toronto Sun|date=5 December 2015}}</ref> Since 2017 taking more than one seat is forbidden by [[Madrid Municipal Transport Company]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/06/08/europe/madrid-manspreading-transit-trnd/index.html|title='Manspreading' is now a no-no on Madrid's public buses|author=Julia Jones|website=CNN|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref> In some cases, people who find manspreading offensive have taken to photographing manspreading, and posting those images on the Internet.<ref name=\"nytsimmons\" />\n\n==Controversy==\n\nBoth this posture and the use of the [[neologism]] \"manspreading\" have occasioned some internet criticism and debates in the US, UK, Turkey, and Canada.<ref>Radhika Sanghani, [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/womens-life/11309866/Ban-manspreading-Brits-want-men-to-sit-with-their-legs-together.html \"'Ban manspreading': Londoners want men to sit with their legs together on the Tube\"], ''The Telegraph'', 23 December 2014.</ref><ref name=\"Seattle\">{{Cite news|last=Johnson|first=Eric M.|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/01/17/us-usa-transportation-manspreading-idUSKBN0KQ01120150117|title=One body, one seat: Seattle's campaign against the 'manspreading' scourge|date=16 January 2015|work=|access-date=|publisher=Reuters}}</ref> \n\nThe criticism and campaigns against manspreading have been counter-criticized for not addressing similar behavior by women, such as taking up adjacent seats with bags, or \"she-bagging.\" The controversy surrounding manspreading has been described by [[equity feminist]] [[Cathy Young]] as \"pseudo feminism \u2013 preoccupied with male misbehavior, no matter how trivial.\"<ref name=\":0\">Cathy Young, [http://www.newsday.com/opinion/columnists/cathy-young/manspreading-but-women-hog-subway-space-too-cathy-young-1.9776186 \"'Manspreading'? But women hog subway space, too\"], ''Newsday'', 5 January 2015.</ref> Twitter-campaigns with the hashtag #manspreading have also been accompanied by hashtags like #shebagging.<ref name=\"Crane\">{{cite news|last1=Crane|first1=Emily|title=Are you a man-spreader or a she-bagger? As the U.S. makes selfish behaviour on public transport a criminal offence \u2013 Australian commuters think it might be time to follow suit|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3110093/Are-man-spreader-bagger-U-S-brings-laws-banning-practice-Australian-commuters-think-time-follow-them.html|accessdate=5 December 2015|publisher=Daily Mail |location= Australia|date=3 June 2015}}</ref> The practice of posting pictures of manspreading taken on subways, buses, and other modes of transportation online has been described as a form of [[online shaming|public shaming]].<ref name=\"Public Shaming\">{{cite web|last1=Devon|first1=Natasha|title=The rise of stranger shaming: How humiliating others became acceptable|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/features/the-rise-of-stranger-shaming-how-humiliating-others-became-acceptable-9982260.html|work=The Independent |date=16 January 2015}}</ref> As an example, in New York, actor [[Tom Hanks]] was photographed on the subway, taking up two seats and criticized for it. He responded on a talk show, \"Hey Internet, you idiot! The train was half empty! It was scattered \u2013 there was plenty of room!\"<ref name=\"Hanks\">{{cite news|last1=Brown|first1=Laurel|title=Tom Hanks defends his 'manspreading' subway style on James Corden's Late Late Show debut|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3009585/Tom-Hanks-defends-manspreading-subway-style-James-Corden-s-Late-Late-debut.html|accessdate=8 December 2015|publisher=The Daily Mail |location= UK|date=24 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Friedman|first1=Megan|title=Tom Hanks Defends His \"Manspreading\" Subway Habit|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a27445/tom-hanks-manspreading-subway/|website=Elle.com|publisher=Hearst Publishing|accessdate=19 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Canadian Association for Equality]] (CAFE), a Canadian [[men's rights group]], has been critical of campaigns against manspreading by transit authorities. The CAFE has argued that it is \"physically painful for men to close their legs\" and that campaigns against manspreading is comparable to \"[forcing] women to stop breast feeding on busses (sic) or trains...\".<ref name=\"star\">{{cite news|last1=Otis|first1=Daniel|title=Man-spreading, a transit controversy with legs|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2014/12/28/manspreading_a_transit_controversy_with_legs.html|accessdate=8 December 2015|publisher=The Toronto Star|date=28 December 2014}}</ref> Commentators in media have made similar arguments regarding the need for men to spread their legs to properly accommodate their [[testicles]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11374213/Is-the-manspreading-campaign-just-prejudice-against-big-guys.html|title=Is the 'manspreading' campaign just prejudice against big guys?|first=Gareth|last=May|publisher=The Telegraph|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=2016-07-12}}</ref> although there is no medical reason to justify the behaviour <ref name=\"nytsimmons\" />. It has also been argued that judging by the number of men who manage to sit without spreading their legs there is no physical impediment <ref name=\":1\" />. Peter Post, the author of the book \u201cEssential Manners for Men\u201d  has been sited as saying that the proper way for men to sit is with their legs parallel rather than in a V-shape <ref name=\"nytsimmons\" /> \n\nIn 2016, the word appeared on [[Lake Superior State University]]'s list of \"banished\" words and phrases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/01/us/banished-words-lake-superior-state-university.html|title='Manspreading', 'Vape' and 'So': Hated words for 2016|first=Christine|last=Hauser|publisher=The New York Times|date=31 December 2015|accessdate=2016-07-12}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2019, two women received criticism for a \"womanspreading\" banner that they displayed on a feminist march in Pakistan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/stories-47832236|title=The 'womanspreading' placard that caused fury in Pakistan|last=Ebrahim|first=Ammar|date=6 April 2019|work=[[BBC News]]|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Social signalling==\nSitting more expansively may signal dominance and sexual attractiveness for males.  Tanya Vacharkulksemsuk, a [[University of California, Berkeley|UC Berkeley]] post-doctorate researcher recently published studies that found spreading out legs and arms is more sexually attractive when males do it.  Using photographs, she found that images of men spreading out got 87% of interest among female viewers.  Expansive poses were not as effective for women, who appeared \"vulnerable\" and \"starfish-like\" according to other researchers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Khazan|first1=Olga|title=Does Manspreading Work?|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2016/03/is-manspreading-sexy/475728/|website=The Atlantic|accessdate=15 May 2016|date=29 March 2016}}</ref> On the other hand, some analysts have found that women sitting cross-legged may be perceived positively as an expression of femininity.<ref>Burns\u2010Ardolino, Wendy A. (2003). \"Reading woman: Displacing the foundations of femininity.\" ''Hypatia'' 18.3 (2003): 42\u201359.</ref> The opposite seating posture to manspreading, leg-crossing, is often viewed as effeminate.<ref>Barlow, David H., E. Joyce Reynolds, and W. Stewart Agras. \"Gender identity change in a transsexual.\" ''Archives of General Psychiatry'' 28.4 (1973): 569\u201376.</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{portal|Transport}}\n* [[Manterrupting]]\n* [[Mansplaining]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Manspreading}}\n{{wiktionary|manspreading}}\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/radio/q/q-schedule-for-monday-april-13-2015-1.3030240/why-nyc-s-campaign-against-manspreading-hit-a-nerve-1.3030491 Why NYC's campaign against \"manspreading\" hit a nerve] Q on CBC\n* [http://www.salon.com/2015/04/15/comedy_troupe_takes_on_the_scourge_of_manspreading_%E2%80%94_by_throwing_a_pizza_party Comedy troupe takes on the scourge of \"manspreading\" \u2013 by throwing a pizza party]\n* Gabrielle Moss, [http://www.bustle.com/articles/34279-why-do-guys-spread-their-legs-when-sitting-on-the-subway-my-weekend-of-sitting-like \"Why Do Guys Spread Their Legs When Sitting on The Subway? My Weekend of Sitting Like a Man\"], ''Bustle''\n\n[[Category:Feminist terminology]]\n[[Category:Men and feminism]]\n[[Category:Neologisms]]\n[[Category:Public transport]]\n[[Category:Sitting]]\n[[Category:Sociolinguistics]]\n[[Category:Words coined in the 2010s]]\n[[Category:Sexism]]\n[[Category:Stereotypes of men]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Practice of sitting in public transport with legs wide apart}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n[[File:Manspreading on Stockholm Metro.jpg|thumb|An example of \"manspreading\" on the [[Stockholm metro]]]]\n'''Manspreading''' or '''man-sitting''' is the practice of men sitting in public transport with legs wide apart, thereby covering more than one seat.<ref name=\"nytsimmons\">{{Cite news |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/21/nyregion/MTA-targets-manspreading-on-new-york-city-subways.html |title = A Scourge Is Spreading. M.T.A.\u2019s Cure? Dude, Close Your Legs. |last = Fitzsimmons |first = Emma G. |date = 20 December 2014 |work =The New York Times | access-date = }}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />. The public debate began when an anti-manspreading campaign started on the [[social media]] website [[Tumblr]] in 2013; the term appeared a year later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.oxforddictionaries.com/2015/09/manspreading-term-popularized-by-mta/|title=Manspreading: how New York City\u2019s MTA popularized a word without actually saying it|author=Katherine Connor Martin|year=2015|publisher=Oxford Dictionaries|accessdate=2016-07-12}}</ref> The journalist Babara Ellen described it in 2013 as \"essentially anger at the space these men feel entitled to take up\". <ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/sep/22/men-legs-splayed-on-train|title=Ellen, Barbara. The real reason men should keep their legs together. The Guardian, Sept 22, 213|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> [[OxfordDictionaries.com]] added the word \"manspreading\" in August 2015.<ref name=\"reuters\">{{Cite news |url = https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/27/us-life-manspread-idUSKCN0QW1Y620150827 |title = Manspreading, hangry, Grexit join Oxford online dictionary |date = 27 August 2015 |work = | access-date = | publisher = Reuters}}\n</ref><ref>\n{{cite web\n|title= New words in oxforddictionaries\n|url= https://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/aug/27/hangry-bants-fatberg-new-words-in-oxforddictionaries\n|accessdate= 28 August 2015\n}}\n</ref>. Manspreading is considered a form of  [[Microaggression]] against women because it is a way of disrespect to their personal space.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewaywomenwork.com/2019/04/5-examples-of-microaggressions-in-the-workplace/|title=Rania H. Anderson, 5 Examples of Microaggressions in the Workplace. Retrieved April 14, 2020|last=https://thewaywomenwork.com/2019/04/5-examples-of-microaggressions-in-the-workplace/|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>. Lyndsay Kirkham, a professor of English at Humber College, called man spreading a metaphor for men being given permission to take up more space in society.<ref name=\"TorontoSun\" />  \n\n==Transit authority responses==\n[[File:EMT Madrid ampl\u00eda su se\u00f1alizaci\u00f3n a bordo del autob\u00fas para evitar el \u201cmanspreading\u201d (01).jpg|thumb|Campaign encouraging respectful posture by [[Empresa Municipal de Transportes de Madrid|Madrid Municipal Transport Company]] in 2017.]]\nIn 2014 the [[Metropolitan Transportation Authority]] (MTA) in the [[New York metropolitan area]] and [[Sound Transit]] of [[Seattle]] instituted poster campaigns encouraging respectful posture when other passengers have to stand due to crowding on buses and trains. The MTA campaign, which criticized many behaviors such as leaning on poles and applying make-up, used the slogan \"Dude, stop the spread please!\"<ref>{{Cite news|last=Tahseen|first=Ismat|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/Mumbais-got-its-own-man-spreaders/articleshow/45609512.cms|title=Mumbai\u2019s got its own 'man-spreaders'|date=23 December 2014|work=The Times of India|access-date=|publisher=}}</ref> . Transport officials in [[Philadelphia]], [[Chicago]] and [[Washington D.C.]] have not noted complaints against manspreading in particular although the [[Philadelphia transportation authority|Philadelphia Transportation Authority]] at that time had an etiquete campaign with the slogan \u201cDude It\u2019s Rude... Two Seats \u2014 Really?\u201d aimed at people who occupied sits with bags. .<ref name=\"nytsimmons\" /> Despite social media pressure and public debate to extend the campaign to the Canadian city of [[Toronto]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://toronto.ctvnews.ca/movement-to-ban-man-spreading-on-transit-picks-up-speed-in-toronto-1.2158517|title=Movement to ban 'man-spreading' on transit picks up speed in Toronto, CTV Toronto\nPublished Monday, December 22, 2014|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/lifestyle/man-spreading-debate-spreads-to-toronto-1.2165494|title=Jesse Tahirali, 'Man-spreading' debate spreads to Toronto. CTV News. Published Monday, December 29, 2014|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>  a representative of the [[Toronto Transit Commission]] stated \u201cWe\u2019re not commenting on the manspreading campaign\", and she reminded the users to be courteous to each other. Allowing someone else to take an empty seat beside them.<ref name = \"TorontoSun\">{{cite news|last1=Yuen|first1=Jenny|title=Anti-'manspreading' campaign called sexist|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2014/12/29/anti-manspreading-campaign-called-sexist|accessdate=5 December 2015|publisher=The Toronto Sun|date=5 December 2015}}</ref> Since 2017 taking more than one seat is forbidden by [[Madrid Municipal Transport Company]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/06/08/europe/madrid-manspreading-transit-trnd/index.html|title='Manspreading' is now a no-no on Madrid's public buses|author=Julia Jones|website=CNN|access-date=2019-01-19}}</ref> In some cases, people who find manspreading offensive have taken to photographing manspreading, and posting those images on the Internet.<ref name=\"nytsimmons\" />\n\n==Controversy==\n[[File:Shebagging_in_London.jpg|thumb|right|Woman on the [[London Underground]], \"she-bagging\" by taking up the adjacent seat. A behavior also seen in men ]]\nBoth this posture and the use of the [[neologism]] \"manspreading\" have occasioned some internet criticism and debates in the US, UK, Turkey, and Canada.<ref>Radhika Sanghani, [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/womens-life/11309866/Ban-manspreading-Brits-want-men-to-sit-with-their-legs-together.html \"'Ban manspreading': Londoners want men to sit with their legs together on the Tube\"], ''The Telegraph'', 23 December 2014.</ref><ref name=\"Seattle\">{{Cite news|last=Johnson|first=Eric M.|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/01/17/us-usa-transportation-manspreading-idUSKBN0KQ01120150117|title=One body, one seat: Seattle's campaign against the 'manspreading' scourge|date=16 January 2015|work=|access-date=|publisher=Reuters}}</ref> \n\nThe criticism and campaigns against manspreading have been counter-criticized for not addressing similar behavior by women, such as taking up adjacent seats with bags, or \"she-bagging.\" The controversy surrounding manspreading has been described by [[equity feminist]] [[Cathy Young]] as \"pseudo feminism \u2013 preoccupied with male misbehavior, no matter how trivial.\"<ref name=\":0\">Cathy Young, [http://www.newsday.com/opinion/columnists/cathy-young/manspreading-but-women-hog-subway-space-too-cathy-young-1.9776186 \"'Manspreading'? But women hog subway space, too\"], ''Newsday'', 5 January 2015.</ref> Twitter-campaigns with the hashtag #manspreading have also been accompanied by hashtags like #shebagging.<ref name=\"Crane\">{{cite news|last1=Crane|first1=Emily|title=Are you a man-spreader or a she-bagger? As the U.S. makes selfish behaviour on public transport a criminal offence \u2013 Australian commuters think it might be time to follow suit|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3110093/Are-man-spreader-bagger-U-S-brings-laws-banning-practice-Australian-commuters-think-time-follow-them.html|accessdate=5 December 2015|publisher=Daily Mail |location= Australia|date=3 June 2015}}</ref> The practice of posting pictures of manspreading taken on subways, buses, and other modes of transportation online has been described as a form of [[online shaming|public shaming]].<ref name=\"Public Shaming\">{{cite web|last1=Devon|first1=Natasha|title=The rise of stranger shaming: How humiliating others became acceptable|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/features/the-rise-of-stranger-shaming-how-humiliating-others-became-acceptable-9982260.html|work=The Independent |date=16 January 2015}}</ref> As an example, in New York, actor [[Tom Hanks]] was photographed on the subway, taking up two seats and criticized for it. He responded on a talk show, \"Hey Internet, you idiot! The train was half empty! It was scattered \u2013 there was plenty of room!\"<ref name=\"Hanks\">{{cite news|last1=Brown|first1=Laurel|title=Tom Hanks defends his 'manspreading' subway style on James Corden's Late Late Show debut|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3009585/Tom-Hanks-defends-manspreading-subway-style-James-Corden-s-Late-Late-debut.html|accessdate=8 December 2015|publisher=The Daily Mail |location= UK|date=24 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Friedman|first1=Megan|title=Tom Hanks Defends His \"Manspreading\" Subway Habit|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a27445/tom-hanks-manspreading-subway/|website=Elle.com|publisher=Hearst Publishing|accessdate=19 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Canadian Association for Equality]] (CAFE), a Canadian [[men's rights group]], has been critical of campaigns against manspreading by transit authorities. The CAFE has argued that it is \"physically painful for men to close their legs\" and that campaigns against manspreading is comparable to \"[forcing] women to stop breast feeding on busses (sic) or trains...\".<ref name=\"star\">{{cite news|last1=Otis|first1=Daniel|title=Man-spreading, a transit controversy with legs|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2014/12/28/manspreading_a_transit_controversy_with_legs.html|accessdate=8 December 2015|publisher=The Toronto Star|date=28 December 2014}}</ref> Commentators in media have made similar arguments regarding the need for men to spread their legs to properly accommodate their [[testicles]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11374213/Is-the-manspreading-campaign-just-prejudice-against-big-guys.html|title=Is the 'manspreading' campaign just prejudice against big guys?|first=Gareth|last=May|publisher=The Telegraph|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=2016-07-12}}</ref> although there is no medical reason to justify the behaviour <ref name=\"nytsimmons\" />. It has also been argued that judging by the number of men who manage to sit without spreading their legs there is no physical impediment <ref name=\":1\" />. Peter Post, the author of the book \u201cEssential Manners for Men\u201d  has been sited as saying that the proper way for men to sit is with their legs parallel rather than in a V-shape <ref name=\"nytsimmons\" /> \n\nIn 2016, the word appeared on [[Lake Superior State University]]'s list of \"banished\" words and phrases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/01/us/banished-words-lake-superior-state-university.html|title='Manspreading', 'Vape' and 'So': Hated words for 2016|first=Christine|last=Hauser|publisher=The New York Times|date=31 December 2015|accessdate=2016-07-12}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2019, two women received criticism for a \"womanspreading\" banner that they displayed on a feminist march in Pakistan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/stories-47832236|title=The 'womanspreading' placard that caused fury in Pakistan|last=Ebrahim|first=Ammar|date=6 April 2019|work=[[BBC News]]|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Social signalling==\nSitting more expansively may signal dominance and sexual attractiveness for males.  Tanya Vacharkulksemsuk, a [[University of California, Berkeley|UC Berkeley]] post-doctorate researcher recently published studies that found spreading out legs and arms is more sexually attractive when males do it.  Using photographs, she found that images of men spreading out got 87% of interest among female viewers.  Expansive poses were not as effective for women, who appeared \"vulnerable\" and \"starfish-like\" according to other researchers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Khazan|first1=Olga|title=Does Manspreading Work?|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2016/03/is-manspreading-sexy/475728/|website=The Atlantic|accessdate=15 May 2016|date=29 March 2016}}</ref> On the other hand, some analysts have found that women sitting cross-legged may be perceived positively as an expression of femininity.<ref>Burns\u2010Ardolino, Wendy A. (2003). \"Reading woman: Displacing the foundations of femininity.\" ''Hypatia'' 18.3 (2003): 42\u201359.</ref> The opposite seating posture to manspreading, leg-crossing, is often viewed as effeminate.<ref>Barlow, David H., E. Joyce Reynolds, and W. Stewart Agras. \"Gender identity change in a transsexual.\" ''Archives of General Psychiatry'' 28.4 (1973): 569\u201376.</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{portal|Transport}}\n* [[Manterrupting]]\n* [[Mansplaining]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Manspreading}}\n{{wiktionary|manspreading}}\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/radio/q/q-schedule-for-monday-april-13-2015-1.3030240/why-nyc-s-campaign-against-manspreading-hit-a-nerve-1.3030491 Why NYC's campaign against \"manspreading\" hit a nerve] Q on CBC\n* [http://www.salon.com/2015/04/15/comedy_troupe_takes_on_the_scourge_of_manspreading_%E2%80%94_by_throwing_a_pizza_party Comedy troupe takes on the scourge of \"manspreading\" \u2013 by throwing a pizza party]\n* Gabrielle Moss, [http://www.bustle.com/articles/34279-why-do-guys-spread-their-legs-when-sitting-on-the-subway-my-weekend-of-sitting-like \"Why Do Guys Spread Their Legs When Sitting on The Subway? My Weekend of Sitting Like a Man\"], ''Bustle''\n\n[[Category:Feminist terminology]]\n[[Category:Men and feminism]]\n[[Category:Neologisms]]\n[[Category:Public transport]]\n[[Category:Sitting]]\n[[Category:Sociolinguistics]]\n[[Category:Words coined in the 2010s]]\n[[Category:Sexism]]\n[[Category:Stereotypes of men]]\n", "name_user": "SoledadMirandaRottmann", "label": "safe", "comment": "Remove a picture that refers to a different term.  I think it is outside the scope of this article. Distract from the main subject.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manspreading"}
